   <h1 class=3D"toggle">Details and Options</h1>
   <div class=3D"NotesThumbnails">
    <img src=3D"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Files/InverseLap=
laceTransform.en/details_1.png" height=3D"70" width=3D"170" alt=3D"">
    <img src=3D"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Files/InverseLap=
laceTransform.en/details_2.png" height=3D"70" width=3D"170" alt=3D"">
   </div>
   <div class=3D"hideable">
    <ul class=3D"functionList">
     <li><a name=3D"822839656"></a>Laplace transforms are typically used to=
 transform differential and partial differential equations to algebraic equ=
ations, solve and then inverse transform back to a solution. </li>
     <li><a name=3D"43533310"></a>Laplace transforms are also extensively u=
sed in control theory and signal processing as a way to represent and manip=
ulate linear systems in the form of transfer functions and transfer matrice=
s. The Laplace transform and its inverse are then a way to transform betwee=
n the time domain and frequency domain. </li>
     <li><a name=3D"30280"></a>The inverse Laplace transform of a function =
<span class=3D"IM"><img src=3D"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/F=
iles/InverseLaplaceTransform.en/3.png" height=3D"15" width=3D"25" alt=3D"">=
</span> is defined to be <span class=3D"IM"><img src=3D"https://reference.w=
olfram.com/language/ref/Files/InverseLaplaceTransform.en/4.png" height=3D"2=
2" width=3D"120" alt=3D""></span>, where <span class=3D"IF"><span class=3D"=
TR"><span class=3D"special-character Gamma">=CE=B3</span></span></span> is =
an arbitrary positive constant chosen so that the contour of integration li=
es to the right of all singularities in <span class=3D"IM"><img src=3D"http=
s://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Files/InverseLaplaceTransform.en/5.p=
ng" height=3D"15" width=3D"25" alt=3D""></span>. </li>
     <img src=3D"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Files/InverseLa=
placeTransform.en/Image_6.gif" height=3D"98" width=3D"130" class=3D"" alt=
=3D"">
     <li><a name=3D"330437221"></a>The multidimensional inverse Laplace tra=
nsform of a function <span class=3D"IM"><img src=3D"https://reference.wolfr=
